Designed to run on multiple cores and to support concurrency.
static type language.
Used for multi-threading.
Used in server-side or backend language.
Go programs are organized into packages.
Go's standard library, provides different core packages for us to use
fmt is one of these, which you can us it by importing it.
A package is a collection of source files.

steps:
go mod init GoLangOp -> To initiate our project

import "fmt"
go run hello.go -> runs the code.

go run main.go deck-receiver.go -> Run two files in same package